<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Turner</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate-General of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-29"><hi rend="italic">April
                                        29, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 25th instant I wired you as
                            follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Cabinet meeting to-day declares Canada to be neutral and in
                                    addition the ordinary enlistment act.</p>
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Turner</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Consul-General.</hi></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I have the honor to inclose herewith the Governor-General’s
                                proclamation<note n="2" xml:id="d719fn2">Not printed, butis in the
                                same terms, mutatis mutandis, as that of Great Britain, (see <ref target="#pg_865">p. 865</ref>), except as to preamble.</note> in
                            reference to the above.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Turner</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Consul-General.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>